data.title: Liberty Hall
data.meta_description: Liberty Hall is a local museum in Kenansville, North Carolina. The restored house is a Southern Historic Landmark welcoming visitors from all over the world.
data.text: The Antebellum South was once treasured for its grace and charm. Liberty Hall in Kenansville, North Carolina stands today as a proud reminder of a time that exists only in history books. Liberty Hall was built in the early 1800's and is the ancestral home of the prominent Kenan family who were among the earliest founders and leaders in Duplin County and the state. The house has been restored and is a Southern Historic Landmark museum, welcoming visitors from all over the world.
